appPrivateFiles.description:
Defines files which are ignored on saving and loading.
The files are matched case-insensitively using regular expressions following the RE2 syntax (https://golang.org/s/re2syntax).
Examples:
"^my-app/[^/]+\\.bak$" would ignore all files with the extension .bak in the "my-app" directory;
"^my-app/tmp/" would ignore the content of "myapp/tmp/";
"^my-app/tmp" would ignore all files and directories whose names start with "myapp/tmp"
